YES, the proposed patch correctly fixes the bug in the original radix sort implementation. The core issue in the buggy code was the use of popping elements from the buckets, which reverses the order of elements within each bucket and breaks the stability of the sort. Stability is crucial in radix sort because the relative order of elements with the same digit must be preserved across passes to ensure correct final ordering. The patch addresses this by iterating over the buckets in order and copying elements back into the list without popping, thus maintaining the original insertion order within each bucket. Additionally, removing the unnecessary tracking of active buckets and simply iterating over all buckets in fixed order simplifies the logic and avoids missing any digits. This change ensures that the sort is stable and correctly handles multi-digit numbers, including those with shared digits at certain places, thereby resolving the failures described in the bug report.
